-- India's Infosys shares slump after board member Srinivas resigns
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed May 28, 2014 11:46PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 29 (Reuters) - Shares in India's Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> fell 4.7 percent at pre-open trading after president and board member B.G. Srinivas, seen by some investors as a candidate to take over as CEO, resigned.

